The reason is that `std::is_constructible` requires a complete type: ([Table 42](https://timsong-cpp.github.io/cppwp/n4659/meta.unary.prop#tab:type-traits.properties))

&gt; ## Template
&gt; 
&gt;     template &lt;class T&gt;
&gt;     struct is_&#173;copy_&#173;constructible;
&gt; 
&gt; ## Preconditions
&gt; 
&gt; `T` shall be a complete type, *cv* void, or an array of unknown bound.

Failing to meet a library &quot;shall&quot; requirement results in undefined behavior.

